      • extractTimestamp

        protected static long extractTimestamp(@Nullable
                                       java.lang.String timestampAttribute,
                                       @Nullable
                                       java.lang.String pubsubTimestamp,
                                       @Nullable
                                       java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> attributes)
        Return the timestamp (in ms since unix epoch) to use for a Pubsub message with attributes and pubsubTimestamp.

        If timestampAttribute is non-null then the message attributes must contain that attribute, and the value of that attribute will be taken as the timestamp. Otherwise the timestamp will be taken from the Pubsub publish timestamp pubsubTimestamp.

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the timestamp cannot be recognized as a ms-since-unix-epoch or RFC3339 time.

                                                                                                    boolean returnImmediately)

      • isEOF

        public abstract boolean isEOF()
        Return true if pull(long, org.apache.beam.sdk.io.gcp.pubsub.PubsubClient.SubscriptionPath, int, boolean) will always return empty list. Actual clients will return false. Test clients may return true to signal that all expected messages have been pulled and the test may complete.
